				<h1>Why choose Wallabies air warmer?</h1>
<p>The normal temperature of the human body ranges between 36.5 degrees to 37.2 degree Celsius. But when the human body goes under the impact of anesthesia, it stops maintaining thermal regulation. Consequently, it hampers the body's function and it becomes unable to maintain the required temperature. This condition is known as hypothermia. It can occur before, during, and after the surgery of patients that is done under influence of anesthesia. Our air warmers are safe and comfortable devices that can prevent the condition of hypothermia. </p>
<p>If you want an efficient solution to prevent such critical body drop conditions for your patients, you can consider our high-tech patient forced air warmer units. These units are laced with the latest technology and features. Hence, the warming process can begin within 30 seconds and the patient can get appropriate heating while lying on the operation table. You will get each unit with a temperature management unit and blower to circulate warm air. The air will be supplied to the patient through the intact filters of the unit. So, you will be able to supply adequate warm air to the patient with a controlled temperature for maximum comfort. </p>
<h1>Why choose Patient forced warmers?</h1>
<p>It is undoubtedly true that hypersensitivity is linked with surgeries. The drop in body temperature before the operation is also associated with the anxiety of patients. Some patients often lose hope to survive before surgery if it is major that can also lead to hypothermia. Well, our patient forced air warmer systems are highly efficient to prevent these instances. They are widely used devices in Ontario, Canada because they really work. Many orthopedic, and cardiac clinics and general surgeons prefer their use for patients to provide them warming comfort. Wallabies is consistently working for the safety of patients and working as a pioneer in this medical device classification. </p>
<h1>Major research about patient forced warming units</h1>
<p>First of all, the use of these devices is authenticated and validated with research by the experts. They have mentioned that the use of warming units before and during surgery can actually reduce surgical site infection rates. Apart from comfort and safety, it also works to reduce the risk of blood loss, shorten the length of hospital stays, and avoid unnecessary costs. You can even check patients’ testimonials on how these devices have provided them with wholesome comfort during the time of stay at hospitals. </p>
